Plan

  • A logistic regression as evaluation process

A Logistic Regression

Recall: a logistic regression divides 2 sets by a line (or a hyperplane if we have higher dimensions)

The logistic regression formula: \[ Z = \frac{1}{1+\text{exp}(-[b_0+b_1X + b_2Y])} \]

Sigmoid function a.k.a. activation function: \[ S(t) = \frac{1}{1+\text{exp}(-t)}=\frac{1}{1+e^{-t}} \]

A Logistic Regression as a Evaluation on a scale from 0 to 1

Problem to evaluate:
A sufficient range of goods for a week

Combined Linear Regressions as a Chain of Command

a) A sufficient range of goods for a week

b) An optimal storage fill

A Chain of Command: Information Flow

a) a sufficient goods range
b) an optimal storage fill



1) Information is gathered, processed and handed to higher level: a forward propagation

2) Instructions for corrections go down: a backward propagation (of errors)

Neural Network: Information Flow

Middle manageres are hidden layers which do the balk of the job

Activation Functions

Relu (Rectified linear unit)

\[ \large{ f(x) =\begin{cases} 0 \text{ for }x < 0\\ x \text{ for }x \geq 0 \end{cases}} \]



Binary Step Function \[ \large{ f(x) =\begin{cases} 0 \text{ for }x < 0\\ 1 \text{ for }x \geq 0 \end{cases}} \]
